<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#707070"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Korihor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">All the necro guides suggest casting your summon pet spell until you summon the best one.<P>How do you know what the best pet is for your level and summon spell?<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Krescent</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Although I am not a strong caster, being only a dabbler in the Necromantic arts as most Shadowknights are.. I am befriended to many casters with pets that safeguard them...  One way you can tell how powerful your pet is is just to con them.  My friend, an elemental mage, gets quite unnerved at times when he considers his pet, and the pet is stronger than he is.. ( nothing like a yellow conned pet.. wheee ^_^ )<P>Ah.. how I wish I could be able to have a pet that strong.. a pet that could protect me without problems.. a pet that *I* don't have to taunt the creatures of *HIM*... at least he's good company to talk to.. he listens wonderfully and laughs quite loudly at my jokes.. <P>Stay safe.. and good journeys..<P><P>------------------<BR>Krescent N'ytte<BR>Guild Leader of Empire of the Damned<BR>21st Rank Shadowknight<BR>Apprentice to Tenr O'Sevn<BR>Teir'Dal <BR>Rodcet Nife</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Sevok Celith'ar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Check the Caster's Realm spell guides - they list the level ranges of pets for each spell.<P>Then you'll know what level pet each spell is capable of producing, and can judge what cons they should be.<P>A word of advice - don't get used to white/yellow pets. =)<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Mekdawa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">With the Leering Corpse spell (level 4 spell) I've been able to produce level 6 pets on many occasions.<P>------------------<BR>------------------<BR>Mekdawa 7th tier Necromancer and child of Innoruuk, the Prince of Hate<BR>Methaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">rach12</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">When it comes to the basics, once you get new spells (ie..8 lvl) you can summon a lvl higher (ie...9 lvl) pet, but you will mostly get lvl 7 and such. So when you get a new pet at 12...you can get a 13th lvl pet. The chances of getting a white conning pet just before making a new spell lvl are nil, they'll alway be blue then.<P>------------------<BR>Take Care<P>Rach12</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
